To list the services use the command service and press <TAB> to show the list of the services

Or you can type the command:

> service --status-all

To check the status, to start or stop the service do the following:

> service ssh status
> service ssh start
> service ssh stop


To install ssh server do the following:

> sudo apt install openssh-server

After installation, ssh server is automatically started, which can be checked with command:

> service ssh status

 
